Post a progress update to Linear.

Usage:
  /progress-update
  /progress-update {{formats.issueExample}}

This command will:
1. Analyze recent commits since last update
2. Check current file changes (git status, git diff)
3. Review acceptance criteria progress from task analysis
4. Generate structured update
5. Post to Linear issue as comment

Update includes:
- Completed items (from recent commits)
- Current work in progress (from file changes)
- Next steps (remaining acceptance criteria)
- Any blockers

Example:
  /progress-update

Claude will analyze your recent work and post a comprehensive update
to the Linear issue you're working on.

Perfect for:
- Daily standup updates
- End of day progress reports
- Before requesting code review
- When switching to another issue
